      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "---\n\n**MEMORANDUM**\n\nTO: Compliance Team  \nFROM: [Your Name]  \nDATE: [Current Date]  \nSUBJECT: Comprehensive KYC Compliance Checklist for New Client Onboarding\n\n---\n\n**I. Introduction**\n\nThis memorandum outlines a comprehensive KYC (Know Your Customer) compliance checklist to ensure adherence to regulatory standards during the onboarding process for new clients. The checklist incorporates all necessary regulatory requirements and legal terminology to facilitate a smooth audit process.\n\n**II. KYC Compliance Checklist**\n\n1. **Customer Identification Program (CIP):**\n   - Collect and verify the following information:\n     - Full Name\n     - Date of Birth\n     - Address\n     - Tax Identification Number (TIN)\n     - Passport Number (if applicable)\n     - Nationality\n     - Social Security Number (SSN) (if applicable)\n     - Proof of Address (utility bill, bank statement, etc.)\n\n2. **Customer Due Diligence (CDD):**\n   - Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk clients, including:\n     - Verification of source of funds\n     - Analysis of transaction patterns\n     - Assessment of risk factors (e.g., politically exposed persons, PEPs)\n     - Ongoing monitoring of transactions\n\n3.",
